Hope, you'll find my work usefull.

Here are some default bindings:

==== Client keys:

altkey+` - show client context menu
Ctrl+modkey+d - client settings keymode

==== Tag keys:

altkey+F1 - jump to one tag left
altkey+F2 - jump to one tag right
modkey+F1 - move current clinet one tag left
modkey+F2 - move current clinet one tag right

altkey+tab - toggle last 2 active clients

Crtl+modkey+s - tag manipulation keymode (rename, add, del, etc)

==== Menus:

altkey+Esc - show main menu

There are vim keybindings defained in menus (hjkl - move, o - open, Enter - open)

Mail bugs to ierton@gmail.com.

Sergey.
